main event: A military radar detected an unidentified object over the Pacific Ocean on May 8, 1963.
interesting points: The object was detected on radar moving at speeds up to 1,800 knots (over 2,000 mph) and between altitudes of 2,000 to 60,000 feet.
The radar track was established from coordinates 30-50N 169-00W to 34-20N 175-10W over a 25-minute period.
A visual sighting of the object was not obtained.
The radar contact was lost at 1955Z and no other reports were received.
The case was classified as Insufficient data to identify or classify after the investigation was completed.
